Minister of Health, Zweli Mkhize, briefs the media after South Africa confirmed its third COVID-19 case. Courtesy #DStv403 Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Health, Zweli Mkhize, is expected to brief the public after South Africa confirmed its third COVID-19 case. The third patient is the wife of the first man diagnosed after returning from Italy. On Saturday, South Africa confirmed its second COVID-19 case. Mkhize, says those who have been in contact with the infected couple have been traced and tested. The ministry has asked for calm. 